WEBVTT

00:00:01.280 --> 00:00:06.240
<v Teacher><i>To know</i> in Spanish is <b>saber</b>. <b>Saber.</b>

00:00:06.240 --> 00:00:07.040
<v Student><b>Saber.</b>

00:00:07.840 --> 00:00:12.160
<v Teacher>You may have heard in British slang <i>He's got savvy, she's got savvy</i>.

00:00:12.160 --> 00:00:13.120
<v Teacher>Have you ever heard that?

00:00:13.120 --> 00:00:13.760
<v Student>Yeah.

00:00:13.740 --> 00:00:15.660
<v Teacher>And that comes from Latin actually.

00:00:15.660 --> 00:00:17.420
<v Teacher>That slang is coming from Latin.

00:00:17.420 --> 00:00:18.940
<v Teacher><b>Saber</b> is <i>to know</i>.

00:00:18.940 --> 00:00:20.300
<v Teacher>He's got <b>saber</b>.

00:00:20.300 --> 00:00:21.740
<v Teacher>He's got <i>savvy</i>.

00:00:21.760 --> 00:00:26.320
<v Teacher><b>Saber</b> is spelt with a <i>b</i>, but in English we're saying <i>savvy</i> with a /v/.

00:00:26.320 --> 00:00:34.240
<v Teacher>So we're seeing even that connection between the sounds of <i>v</i> and <i>b</i> crossing between English and Spanish. <b>Saber</b>, <i>savvy</i>.

00:00:34.240 --> 00:00:36.480
<v Teacher>So <b>saber</b> is <i>to know</i>.

00:00:35.800 --> 00:00:39.079
<v Teacher>So if you want to say <i>I want to know</i>?

00:00:39.079 --> 00:00:40.920
<v Student><b>Quiero saber.</b>

00:00:40.920 --> 00:00:43.800
<v Teacher>How would you say <i>I don't want to know</i>?

00:00:44.020 --> 00:00:44.980
<v Student><b>No quiero saber.</b>

00:00:45.140 --> 00:00:45.460
<v Teacher>Good.

00:00:45.460 --> 00:00:48.660
<v Teacher>How would you say <i>he wants to know</i> or <i>she wants to know</i>

00:00:48.660 --> 00:00:50.900
<v Teacher>or <i>you</i> (formal) <i>want to know</i>?

00:00:52.540 --> 00:00:53.180
<v Student><b>Quiere saber.</b>

00:00:53.180 --> 00:00:53.500
<v Teacher>Good.

00:00:53.500 --> 00:00:56.460
<v Teacher>You change the <i>-o</i> to <i>-e</i>. And you get <b>quiere</b>.

00:00:56.460 --> 00:00:57.500
<v Teacher><b>Quiere saber.</b>

00:00:57.500 --> 00:00:59.899
<v Teacher><i>He doesn't want to know:</i>

00:00:59.899 --> 00:01:01.100
<v Student><b>No quiere saber.</b>

00:01:01.100 --> 00:01:03.100
<v Teacher><i>Why doesn't he want to know?:</i>

00:01:03.540 --> 00:01:04.620
<v Student><b>¿Por qué no quiere saber?</b>

00:01:04.620 --> 00:01:08.060
<v Teacher><i>I want to know why he doesn't want to know:</i>

00:01:08.900 --> 00:01:11.260
<v Student><b>Quiero saber por qué no quiere saber.</b>

00:01:11.260 --> 00:01:12.060
<v Teacher>Very good.

00:01:15.260 --> 00:01:15.980
<v Teacher>Very good.

00:01:16.220 --> 00:01:21.020
<v Teacher>The word for <i>yes</i> in Spanish is <b>sí</b>.

00:01:21.020 --> 00:01:21.980
<v Student><b>Si.</b>

00:01:21.980 --> 00:01:24.300
<v Teacher>This is also the word for <i>if</i>.

00:01:24.840 --> 00:01:26.360
<v Teacher>So how do you say <i>if</i>?

00:01:26.360 --> 00:01:26.920
<v Student><b>Si.</b>

00:01:26.920 --> 00:01:27.640
<v Teacher>Good.

00:01:27.640 --> 00:01:30.840
<v Teacher><i>I want to know if you want to know.</i>

00:01:30.840 --> 00:01:32.200
<v Teacher>Of course we're speaking formally.

00:01:32.200 --> 00:01:33.799
<v Teacher>This is the one we've learned so far.

00:01:33.799 --> 00:01:36.520
<v Teacher><i>I want to know if you want to know:</i>

00:01:37.259 --> 00:01:40.539
<v Student><b>Quiero saber si quiere saber.</b>

00:01:40.539 --> 00:01:41.259
<v Teacher>Good.

00:01:41.259 --> 00:01:43.820
<v Teacher><b>Quiero saber si quiere saber.</b>

00:01:43.820 --> 00:01:47.820
<v Teacher><i>I want to know if he wants to invite me</i>.

00:01:47.820 --> 00:01:51.179
<v Teacher>So the first bit is <i>I want to know:</i>

00:01:51.920 --> 00:01:53.760
<v Student><b>Quiero saber.</b>

00:01:53.760 --> 00:01:56.560
<v Teacher><b>Saber</b>, <i>b</i> sound 'cause it's a <i>b</i> here.

00:01:56.560 --> 00:01:57.760
<v Student><b>Quiero saber.</b>

00:01:57.760 --> 00:01:58.500
<v Teacher><i>If:</i>

00:01:58.500 --> 00:01:59.100
<v Student><b>Si.</b>

00:01:59.100 --> 00:02:00.600
<v Teacher><i>He wants to invite me:</i>

00:02:00.600 --> 00:02:03.280
<v Student><b>Quiere invitarme.</b>

00:02:06.159 --> 00:02:10.239
<v Teacher>So you see if you think about it block by block, it's very simple.

00:02:10.239 --> 00:02:15.120
<v Teacher>If we think slowly, we learn very quickly and the process gets much faster.

00:02:15.120 --> 00:02:17.200
<v Teacher>How do you say <i>imagination</i>?

00:02:18.060 --> 00:02:19.820
<v Student><b>Imaginación.</b>

00:02:19.820 --> 00:02:20.460
<v Teacher>Good.

00:02:20.460 --> 00:02:22.140
<v Teacher>I don't want to imagine.

00:02:22.140 --> 00:02:23.740
<v Teacher>I don't want to imagine it:

00:02:25.140 --> 00:02:26.900
<v Student><b>No quiero imaginarlo.</b>

00:02:26.900 --> 00:02:27.459
<v Teacher>Good.

00:02:27.700 --> 00:02:29.060
<v Teacher>And what was <i>to come</i>?

00:02:29.060 --> 00:02:34.819
<v Teacher>And we said that we could remember it if we look at <i>convenient</i>, <b>conveniente</b>, which is like "with coming".

00:02:34.819 --> 00:02:35.459
<v Student><b>Venir.</b>

00:02:35.459 --> 00:02:36.340
<v Teacher><b>Venir</b>.

00:02:36.340 --> 00:02:37.299
<v Teacher>Good.

00:02:37.320 --> 00:02:45.560
<v Teacher>I want to know if she wants to come to the house to visit me.

00:02:45.560 --> 00:02:50.120
<v Teacher>I want to know if she wants to come to the house to visit me.

00:02:49.920 --> 00:02:58.320
<v Teacher>So again it might be something that looks overwhelming that we can't say. But if we divide it up: <i>I want to know:</i>

00:02:58.320 --> 00:03:00.080
<v Student><b>Quiero saber.</b>

00:03:00.080 --> 00:03:00.700
<v Teacher><i>If:</i>

00:03:00.700 --> 00:03:01.300
<v Student><b>Si.</b>

00:03:01.980 --> 00:03:02.700
<v Teacher><i>She wants to come:</i>

00:03:02.700 --> 00:03:05.500
<v Student><b>Quiere venir.</b>

00:03:05.500 --> 00:03:06.500
<v Teacher>Good. <i>To the house:</i>

00:03:10.540 --> 00:03:11.900
<v Student><b>A la casa.</b>

00:03:11.900 --> 00:03:12.380
<v Teacher>Good.

00:03:12.380 --> 00:03:13.500
<v Teacher><i>To visit me:</i>

00:03:15.060 --> 00:03:17.380
<v Student><b>A visitarme.</b>

00:03:17.380 --> 00:03:19.060
<v Teacher>Good! You put <b>a</b> there.

00:03:19.060 --> 00:03:21.140
<v Teacher>Because even though we have <b>a la casa</b>,

00:03:22.120 --> 00:03:31.560
<v Teacher>there in between, you stayed with the feeling of <b>venir</b> and you wanted to connect it to the next verb. And you are 100% correct to do that.

00:03:31.560 --> 00:03:36.760
<v Teacher>I want to know why she doesn't want to come to the house to visit me.

00:03:37.580 --> 00:03:44.620
<v Teacher>I want to know why she doesn't want to come to the house to visit me.

00:03:44.620 --> 00:03:46.140
<v Teacher><i>I want to know:</i>

00:03:46.980 --> 00:03:48.420
<v Student><b>Quiero saber.</b>

00:03:48.420 --> 00:03:49.380
<v Teacher><b>SaBer.</b>

00:03:49.380 --> 00:03:50.500
<v Student><b>Quiero saber.</b>

00:03:50.500 --> 00:03:52.020
<v Teacher><i>Why:</i>

00:03:52.020 --> 00:03:53.200
<v Student><b>Por qué.</b>

00:03:53.200 --> 00:03:55.700
<v Teacher><i>She doesn't want:</i>

00:03:55.700 --> 00:03:56.700
<v Student><b>No quiere.</b>

00:03:56.700 --> 00:03:59.060
<v Teacher><i>To come to the house:</i>

00:03:59.980 --> 00:04:01.740
<v Student><b>Venir a la casa.</b>

00:04:01.740 --> 00:04:03.260
<v Teacher><i>To visit me:</i>

00:04:03.260 --> 00:04:04.540
<v Student><b>A visitarme.</b>

00:04:04.540 --> 00:04:05.260
<v Teacher>Good.

00:04:05.260 --> 00:04:06.220
<v Teacher>Very good.

00:04:06.220 --> 00:04:07.260
<v Teacher>Well done.

00:04:07.580 --> 00:04:13.660
<v Teacher><b>Quiero saber por qué no quiere venir a la casa a visitarme</b>.

00:04:13.420 --> 00:04:14.780
<v Teacher>Very good.

00:04:14.780 --> 00:04:28.060
<v Teacher>So what we most want to take away from this is the confidence to try to say what we are almost sure we cannot say. Because we have this wonderful advantage

00:04:27.720 --> 00:04:37.080
<v Teacher>as English speakers, that we have so much vocabulary that we can convert over to Spanish that we won't realize we can convert over to Spanish until we try it.

00:04:37.360 --> 00:04:42.639
<v Teacher>I'll just give you now a couple of sentences for listening practice.

00:04:42.639 --> 00:04:44.479
<v Teacher>What does it mean if I say

00:04:44.720 --> 00:04:52.080
<v Teacher><b>Voy a invitarlo, pero no voy a invitarlo ahora</b>?

00:04:52.080 --> 00:04:53.280
<v Teacher>What did I say?

00:04:53.280 --> 00:04:56.720
<v Teacher>First bit is <b>Voy a invitarlo</b>:

00:04:57.340 --> 00:04:59.420
<v Student><i>I'm going to invite them</i>.

00:04:59.420 --> 00:04:59.980
<v Teacher><b>Lo.</b>

00:04:59.980 --> 00:05:00.860
<v Student>Oh, <i>you</i>.

00:05:01.100 --> 00:05:01.420
<v Teacher>It could be <i>you</i>.

00:05:01.420 --> 00:05:02.700
<v Teacher><i>You</i> formal.

00:05:02.780 --> 00:05:04.140
<v Student><i>You</i> formal or <i>him</i>.

00:05:04.140 --> 00:05:04.780
<v Teacher>Yeah.

00:05:04.860 --> 00:05:05.900
<v Teacher><b>Voy a invitarlo</b>.

00:05:05.740 --> 00:05:06.460
<v Student>Or <i>it</i>?

00:05:06.460 --> 00:05:08.380
<v Teacher>Or <i>it</i> if it can make some sense.

00:05:08.620 --> 00:05:10.700
<v Teacher><i>I'm going to invite it</i>.

00:05:10.440 --> 00:05:15.240
<v Teacher><b>Voy a invitarlo, pero</b>. What is <b>pero</b>?

00:05:15.240 --> 00:05:15.800
<v Student><i>But</i>.

00:05:15.800 --> 00:05:16.400
<v Teacher><i>But</i>.

00:05:16.400 --> 00:05:20.680
<v Teacher><b>No voy a invitarlo ahora</b>:

00:05:21.180 --> 00:05:24.220
<v Student><i>But I won't invite him now</i>.

00:05:24.220 --> 00:05:25.580
<v Teacher>Very good.

00:05:25.580 --> 00:05:28.060
<v Teacher><b>Quiero iniciarlo ahora.</b>

00:05:28.060 --> 00:05:30.940
<v Teacher><b>Quiero iniciarlo ahora</b>:

00:05:31.320 --> 00:05:33.080
<v Student><i>I want to start now.</i>

00:05:33.080 --> 00:05:33.720
<v Teacher>Good.

00:05:33.720 --> 00:05:35.640
<v Teacher>And something missing though.

00:05:35.640 --> 00:05:37.800
<v Teacher><b>Quiero iniciarlo ahora</b>:

00:05:38.120 --> 00:05:39.640
<v Student>Ah. <i>I want to start it now.</i>

00:05:39.640 --> 00:05:40.200
<v Teacher>Good.

00:05:40.280 --> 00:05:42.600
<v Teacher><b>Quiere iniciarlo ahora.</b>

00:05:42.920 --> 00:05:45.080
<v Teacher><b>Quiere iniciarlo ahora</b>:

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:47.760
<v Student><i>You want</i> or <i>he wants.</i>

00:05:47.760 --> 00:05:48.240
<v Teacher>Good.

00:05:48.240 --> 00:05:48.960
<v Student>Or <i>she wants.</i>

00:05:48.960 --> 00:05:53.200
<v Teacher><b>¿Por qué no quiere informarme?</b>

00:05:53.200 --> 00:05:58.440
<v Teacher><b>Por qué no quiere informarme?:</b>

00:05:58.440 --> 00:06:01.080
<v Student><i>Why doesn't he want to let me know?</i>

00:06:01.080 --> 00:06:01.960
<v Student><i>To inform me?</i>

00:06:01.960 --> 00:06:02.759
<v Teacher>Yeah. Perfect.

00:06:02.759 --> 00:06:04.039
<v Teacher>But this is perfect what you did.

00:06:04.039 --> 00:06:07.560
<v Teacher>You found the meaning, but you said it how it's comfortable for you in English.

00:06:07.560 --> 00:06:07.960
<v Teacher>Exactly.

00:06:07.960 --> 00:06:09.240
<v Teacher><i>Why doesn't he want to inform me?</i>

00:06:09.240 --> 00:06:10.840
<v Teacher><i>Why doesn't he want to let me know?</i>

00:06:10.840 --> 00:06:11.720
<v Teacher>Perfect.

00:06:11.820 --> 00:06:16.140
<v Teacher>How is <i>justification</i> in Spanish?

00:06:16.140 --> 00:06:18.060
<v Student>Is it a /kh/ sound?

00:06:18.060 --> 00:06:18.700
<v Teacher>Good,

00:06:18.700 --> 00:06:19.340
<v Teacher>yes.

00:06:19.340 --> 00:06:20.500
<v Teacher>If it's /j/.

00:06:20.500 --> 00:06:22.200
<v Student>So it's <b>justificación</b>?

00:06:22.200 --> 00:06:26.460
<v Teacher><b>Justificación</b>. <i>To justify</i>:

00:06:26.360 --> 00:06:27.479
<v Student><b>Justificar.</b>

00:06:27.479 --> 00:06:28.759
<v Teacher><b>Justificar.</b>

00:06:28.759 --> 00:06:31.639
<v Teacher>I'm not trying to justify myself.

00:06:31.639 --> 00:06:35.319
<v Teacher>I'm not trying to justify myself.

00:06:34.880 --> 00:06:36.960
<v Teacher>What is <i>myself</i> in Spanish?

00:06:36.960 --> 00:06:37.600
<v Student><b>Me.</b>

00:06:37.600 --> 00:06:39.199
<v Teacher>Yes. Same as <i>me</i>.

00:06:39.199 --> 00:06:40.080
<v Teacher>Same as <i>me</i>.

00:06:40.080 --> 00:06:42.800
<v Teacher>So, <i>I'm not trying:</i>

00:06:42.860 --> 00:06:46.460
<v Student><b>No intento justificarlo</b>.

00:06:46.460 --> 00:06:48.699
<v Student>No. <b>Justificarme.</b>

00:06:48.699 --> 00:06:49.340
<v Teacher>Good.

00:06:49.340 --> 00:06:52.699
<v Teacher><b>No intento justificarme</b>.

00:06:52.880 --> 00:06:55.520
<v Teacher><i>But I want to explain</i>.

00:06:55.520 --> 00:06:58.479
<v Teacher>Now <i>explain</i> is an exception.

00:06:58.479 --> 00:07:05.199
<v Teacher>We have <i>explanation</i> in English. But this in Spanish is <b>explicación</b>.

00:07:05.220 --> 00:07:06.180
<v Teacher>It changes,

00:07:06.180 --> 00:07:07.380
<v Teacher>so it's an exception.

00:07:07.380 --> 00:07:10.500
<v Teacher>We don't say <b>explanación</b>, but <b>explicación</b>.

00:07:10.500 --> 00:07:11.860
<v Teacher>We have this in English as well.

00:07:11.860 --> 00:07:14.020
<v Teacher>We have in English <i>inexplicable</i>.

00:07:14.020 --> 00:07:16.180
<v Teacher>How do you say that in Spanish?

00:07:16.180 --> 00:07:17.720
<v Student><b>Inexplicable.</b>

00:07:17.720 --> 00:07:18.360
<v Teacher>Yes.

00:07:18.360 --> 00:07:22.199
<v Teacher>We have it in English this root of the <i>c</i> sound with <i>explain</i>.

00:07:22.199 --> 00:07:25.000
<v Teacher>We say <i>explain</i>, but then we say <i>inexplicable</i>.

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:28.520
<v Teacher>So <i>explanation</i> is <b>explicación</b> in Spanish.

00:07:28.520 --> 00:07:30.440
<v Teacher>So how is <i>to explain</i>?

00:07:31.180 --> 00:07:32.220
<v Student><b>Explicar.</b>

00:07:32.220 --> 00:07:33.180
<v Teacher><b>Explicar</b>.

00:07:33.180 --> 00:07:36.379
<v Teacher>So <i>but I want to explain:</i>

00:07:36.699 --> 00:07:38.940
<v Student><b>Pero quiero explicar.</b>

00:07:38.940 --> 00:07:39.340
<v Teacher>Good.

00:07:39.340 --> 00:07:41.819
<v Teacher>Do you remember how to say <i>something</i>?

00:07:42.080 --> 00:07:42.800
<v Student><b>Algo.</b>

00:07:42.800 --> 00:07:44.000
<v Teacher><b>Algo.</b> Well done.

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:46.560
<v Teacher><i>But I want to explain you something</i>.

00:07:46.560 --> 00:07:50.640
<v Teacher>In English maybe it's more common we would say <i>I want to explain something to you</i>.

00:07:50.640 --> 00:07:52.720
<v Teacher>But in Spanish we can just say But

00:07:52.940 --> 00:07:56.700
<v Teacher><i>I want to explain you something</i>. And let's say it informally.

00:07:56.700 --> 00:07:59.580
<v Teacher>So what was the word for <i>you</i>, for informal?

00:07:59.580 --> 00:08:00.700
<v Teacher>We can remember it from <i>I love you</i>.

00:08:00.700 --> 00:08:01.400
<v Student><b>Te.</b>

00:08:01.400 --> 00:08:03.740
<v Teacher>Yes. <b>Te. Te quiero.</b>

00:08:03.620 --> 00:08:07.379
<v Teacher>So <i>but I want to explain you something</i>.

00:08:07.379 --> 00:08:10.819
<v Student><b>Pero quiero explicarte algo.</b>

00:08:10.819 --> 00:08:11.699
<v Teacher>Very good.

00:08:13.780 --> 00:08:15.539
<v Teacher>Let's say it all together.

00:08:15.139 --> 00:08:21.380
<v Teacher><i>I'm not trying to justify myself, but I want to explain something to you</i>.

00:08:22.020 --> 00:08:24.259
<v Teacher>So <i>I'm not trying</i> is the first bit.

00:08:24.259 --> 00:08:27.540
<v Teacher>Now I want 100% of your mental energy on

00:08:27.840 --> 00:08:29.040
<v Teacher><i>I'm not trying</i>.

00:08:29.040 --> 00:08:31.200
<v Teacher>All of your attention on <i>I'm not trying</i>

00:08:31.200 --> 00:08:34.160
<v Teacher>then we look at the next bit and we forget <i>I'm not trying</i>.

00:08:34.160 --> 00:08:36.080
<v Teacher>Once we've said it, we don't need to hold it.

00:08:36.080 --> 00:08:37.840
<v Teacher><i>I'm not trying:</i>

00:08:37.840 --> 00:08:39.200
<v Student><b>No intento.</b>

00:08:39.200 --> 00:08:40.880
<v Teacher><i>To justify myself:</i>

00:08:41.640 --> 00:08:43.560
<v Student><b>Justificarme.</b>

00:08:43.560 --> 00:08:45.320
<v Teacher>Good. We can forget that bit.

00:08:45.320 --> 00:08:46.200
<v Teacher><i>But:</i>

00:08:46.200 --> 00:08:46.900
<v Student><b>Pero.</b>

00:08:46.900 --> 00:08:47.700
<v Teacher><i>I want:</i>

00:08:47.700 --> 00:08:48.500
<v Student><b>Quiero.</b>

00:08:48.500 --> 00:08:51.560
<v Teacher><i>To explain you:</i>

00:08:51.560 --> 00:08:53.300
<v Student><b>Explicarte.</b>

00:08:53.300 --> 00:08:54.500
<v Teacher><i>Something:</i>

00:08:57.380 --> 00:08:58.019
<v Student><b>Algo.</b>

00:08:58.019 --> 00:08:58.980
<v Teacher>Very good.

00:08:59.300 --> 00:09:05.700
<v Teacher><b>No intento justificarme, pero quiero explicarte algo.</b>

00:09:05.700 --> 00:09:06.420
<v Teacher>Very good.

00:09:06.420 --> 00:09:07.540
<v Teacher>Well done.
